-- Saudi Civil Aviation $4 Billion Sukuk May Be Priced to Yield 2.75% to 3%
-- B y   D a n a   E l   B a l t a j i
-- 2012-01-15T08:07:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-15/saudi-civil-aviation-4-billion-sukuk-may-be-priced-to-yield-2-75-to-3-.html
The 10-year Islamic bonds of  Saudi
Arabia ’s General Authority of Civil Aviation may be priced to
yield 2.75 percent to 3 percent, two investors familiar with the
transaction said.  The authority plans to raise 15 billion riyals ($4 billion)
from the sale that starts today, they said, declining to be
identified because the deal hasn’t been made public.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dana El Baltaji in Dubai at 
 delbaltaji@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
